I believe the mail error queue is held in memory. Basically, we'd run out of memory for our instance, and so mail wasn't going out. I restarted the instance, and then all of the mail in the error queue disappeared. It didn't go out to the users.

I believe it should be persisted somewhere.

If I use markup like this:

{noformat} 
!image.gif|align=left! !image2.gif|align=right! {info}quick brown fox{info}
{noformat} 

then all is well in Firefox, but in IE6 (and IE7) the info box extends all the way to the right of the window, over the top of the right image.

{panel}I am a panel{panel}
{noformat}I am noformat{noformat}

In HTML, the two blocks will be separated by whitespace. In the PDF export, they will run together.

