Right now users can be given permission to delete any page in a space, or no pages in a space. I would like to be able to give users permissions to remove a page that they have created.

The following works:
{panel:title=mytitle | borderStyle=dashed| borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#F7D6C1| bgColor=#FFFFCE}
a block of text surrounded with a *panel*
yet _another_ line
{panel}

But this does not:
{panel | borderStyle=dashed| borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#F7D6C1| bgColor=#FFFFCE}
a block of text surrounded with a *panel*
yet _another_ line
{panel}

The title variable is specified as optional in the documentation, so it would stand to reason that it is optional. Need to fix.

