I have some paths I'm putting into a Conf page that contain environment variables. If I use the {{ }} the \% gets escaped to %, but {noformat} works properly. See these examples:

{{c:\docs\%username%\...}}
{noformat}c:\docs\%username%\...{noformat}

The first fails and prints c:\docs%username%\... but the second succeeds.

Expected: {{ }} should not have any escaping of backslashes inside of it, should it? Seems like it should behave exactly the same as {noformat} except that it's inline.

